  "title": "悬崖上的谋杀",
  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\241-悬崖上的谋杀-阿加莎克里斯蒂.txt",
  "chunk_index": 12,
  "summary": "Frankie, Bobby, and George Abathnot prepare to execute their plan to stage a fake car accident. To facilitate the scheme, Frankie and Bobby visit a garage where they meet a man named Baz, and Frankie purchases a second-hand Standard car for ten pounds. The group coordinates the logistics of the accident, which is designed to make Frankie appear to have suffered a concussion.\n\nThe group meets at a location approximately one mile from Stapleton village, near a sharp turn where the wall of the Merroway estate protrudes. The plan dictates that George will drive his car around the corner and wave a handkerchief to signal that the road is clear. Once Frankie waves her handkerchief from the road, Bobby will release the brakes on the Standard, allowing it to roll down the hill and strike the wall. Bobby intends to steer the car from the footboard before jumping clear to avoid injury.\n\nDuring the execution, George signals that the coast is clear. Bobby steers the accelerating car down the slope and jumps off just before it hits the wall. Frankie runs to the wreckage and sits inside to simulate an injury. George arrives and assists Frankie in making the scene more convincing by creasing her hat to simulate the effects of a concussion. When a seventeen-year-old cyclist arrives and asks if Frankie is dead, George poses as a doctor and instructs the young man to help him carry Frankie to Morrow House, the home of a magistrate named Mr. Baskington-French.",
